headline: IBM (NYSE:IBM) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q4 CY2025, Stock Soars
summary: Technology and consulting giant IBM (NYSE:IBM) reported Q4 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.1% year on year to $19.69 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.52 per share was 5.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: IBM beats fourth-quarter revenue estimates as AI boosts software demand
summary: IBM beat Wall Street estimates for fourth-quarter revenue and profit on Wednesday, as the rapid adoption of artificial intelligence boosts demand for its software services, ranging ​from managing swaths of data to automating IT processes.  Businesses have doubled down on upgrading their software suites to develop data-intensive AI technology, helping sales for IT service ‌and software providers such as IBM.  Sales in its software segment stood at $9.03 billion in the quarter ‍ended December 31, also beating an estimate of $8.77 billion.
